column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I guess I found myself comparing this Hyatt Regency to the San Diego Hyatt Regencies we've stayed at. I could definitely tell this was a former Embassy Suites.  Bartenders were great.  I guess my only complaint was the female front desk clerk who gave me crap about wanting 3 waters for the 3 of us in the room. She made a point of telling me my Discoverist status only allows 2 waters per day. I've never had that experience at any of the other Hyatts I've stayed, including your the Green Bay property when someone else was working.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ;So I don't travel at all so this was a rare occasion, a couple of things came up, I needed to check out early due to storm damage at home, they were very accommodating about this but did not let me know that I would for sure need to check out in person to get this taken care of. I also was charged extra the day I checked in with no explanation of what it was for until I asked. We now have everything figured out and the staff was good about it, I am hoping this may give you an insight into training that not everyone stays at hotels regularly and some extra info might help us non travelers.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ;Found larva moving on top sheet. Bag it while it was still moving and brought it to the attention of the front desk. I then told my husband and told him that I did not think I could sleep in that bed after that. We contacted someone one the state level that work with the convention center and hotel he convinced them to move me to a different  room they did not offer to move most of our stuff. Dinner at restraunt Friday took way to long.they were not really busy but it took almost 45 minutes to a hour . Waitress did not ask those who had soup if we wanted it before the entrees. When the bill came they said sorry for the wait but we had a banquet to take care off. We presenting the card for the free breakfast we were told to present them to the waitress. She said to give them to the other waitresses neither of them took them they told me to present them to the front desk during check out. During check I told them they told me to give the card to front desk they said they were not suppose to do it that way and should of taken it Saturday morning at breakfast. I am not in charge of your employees not knowing what to do. I would not come back to this hotel. If there is a bug or larva live on sheet just think there could be more elsewhere in the room. Bathrooms in the pool area do not have mirrors or a area to charge wher;Yes not lied about not having another room. I then told my husband and told him that I did not think I could sleep in that bed after that. We contacted someone one the state level that work with the convention center and hotel he convinced them to move me to a different  room they did not offer to move most of our stuff. Dinner at restraunt Friday took way to long.they were not really busy but it took almost 45 minutes to a hour . Waitress did not ask those who had soup if we wanted it before the entrees. When the bill came they said sorry for the wait but we had a banquet to take care off. We presenting the card for the free breakfast we were told to present them to the waitress. She said to give them to the other waitresses neither of them took them they told me to present them to the front desk during check out. During check I told them they told me to give the card to front desk they said they were not suppose to do it that way and should of taken it Saturday morning at breakfast. I am not in charge of your employees not knowing what to do. I would not come back to this hotel. If there is a bug or larva live on sheet just think there could be more elsewhere in the room. Bathrooms in the pool area do not have mirrors or a area to charge wher

The Social (formerly Pub 333) Manager Minoj;The members of staff at the Hyatt Regency Hotel Green Bay, especially these seven mentioned earlier, were very welcoming, friendly, courteous and helpful from the moment that I walked into the hotel with my wife for our vacation to celebrate my milestone birthday and attend a church event in Green Bay.

I received complimentary birthday gifts including a beautiful birthday card, greetings, coffee and a $10 voucher to spend in the hotel's Market.

They gave me advice on the local services and attractions like nearby supermarkets, museum, restaurants, car hire services and even heated up my room when I complained that it was too cold. 

I enjoyed using their clean and functioning facilities like their gym, swimming pool, sauna and steam room. 

Needless to say that I thoroughly enjoyed myself and I did not want my 10-day vacation to end as I truly felt at home as the staff catered to all my needs and when spoilt me a lot. 

This is especially after my baggage was lost on my arrival to Green Bay Airport but later found and delivered to me at the hotel by Delta Airlines, who are in partnership with Hyatt Regency Hotel.

I would definitely recommend the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Green Bay, Wisconsin to anyone planning to stay in the area, as I'm already planning to return there myself.

This is also to say a BIG thank you to the amazing staff at the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Green Bay, Wisconsin. You guys are the best. You're awesome! You rock!

Keep up your exceptionally great first-class service.

Your very happy and satisfied guest, Ike.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

; ; ; ; ;What a great stay. Anastasia checked me in, answered all my questions and was very knowledgeable. Subsequent conversations also exceeded my expectations. The food in the restaurant was very good,  however wait times to be waited on after being seated were very long. We ate one breakfast,  lunch and dinner at the hotel, and it was the same long wait times. 

I also talked with the sales director and had a great conversation. She was very helpful, and provided suggestions for getting a reserved year for the model train show. We will not stay anywhere else when in Green Bay!; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column282: My brother passed away, I had to get to my family and when asked if I could check out early due to the circumstances I was told I’m not sure we can turn over the room.  We had come back to the hotel for our bags and the room was already clean.  This was early enough in the day the room could have been still used; however, there wasn’t a demand for the room.  The parking lot was almost empty when we departed.  I just don’t understand why the rate couldn’t have been refunded given the unforeseen circumstances.

column64: ; ; ;We were getting a little chilly in our room and tried to turn the thermostat temperature up a couple of degrees, but it never moved.  When we called down to the front desk, we were told that we did not have control of it and that the hotel controls the thermostats and that they were set on cool, but they could turn off our fan (which would decrease the circulation in the room) and bring up a space heater.  We declined this option that night; however, we asked if we could have the heater brought up in the morning and it never arrived.  We even stopped by the front desk and told them no one had come by and she assured us someone would be to our room within the next 5 minutes with a space heater, and yet, no one showed up.  By that point we were getting ready to check out, so we didn't pursue the request further.  This whole situation was very inconvenient to us as guests of the hotel not being able to control the temperature in our own room.;Guests should be allowed to control their own room temperatures.  There shouldn't be one blanket temperature set across all rooms in the hotel, as each guest requires different heating and cooling needs.  Also, bringing in space heaters/coolers seems a little ridiculous, outdated, and even potentially dangerous if the unit malfunctions.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

; ; ; ; ; ;My husband and I ate a quick dinner on Friday evening, April 11th, seated at the bar in the restaurant. For drinks, we ordered only non-alcolholic:  a coffee and an Arnold Palmer, along with our food. The two bartenders, Isaac and Tristan, were exremely good to us, and very friendly: chatting with us about "this and that" and got our order together very quickly. We were very impressed with their friendliness and sense of humor !

The beds in the room were very comfortable, with firm mattresses and lovely bedding.

Thank you for your usual "Hyatt Excellence" !

Most Sincerely
Nancy Jo and John Baratti in Brookfield, WI; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

My stay was excellent. I am so impressed by the staff who were friendly and polite. The room was very clean and comfortable.
My only slight complaint is that first we were told parking was free but I was charged $10 per night. When I left, it took 35 minutes to get out of the lot. One exit was closed and the other not working properly. That was frustrating

I will definitely return when I am in GrrenBay again.

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;A few disappointments. The hotel is a little bit dated. It's nicely appointed and I like the suites.  But it was not as comfortable as expected. I brought my brother, who is disabled, for his birthday. He got the king bed with the gigantic and wonderful TV, and I slept in the "sitting room" on the sofa sleeper. I can barely walk now, after sleeping on it and driving home yesterday. My lower and upper back are extremely sore. It was also very noisy in the room itself. Cold air blew through the seams around the door to the point that the drapes moved. When someone let their door slam it caused a loud noise that sounded like thunder and rattled everything, scaring my little senior dog and of course people were rude and loud in the hall until very late.  I do not think she relaxed or slept the entire time we were there. She also didn't want to eat. The dog relief area is full of cigarette butts because there was no receptacle for people to use for them. I didn't know I needed to use my parking ticket to get in and out. I thought I was supposed to somehow use my room key. That's on me but it was not clear. 
I bought a sandwich in the snack bar which I assumed was open 24 hours? The server was cleaning everything and when I asked if I could purchase something she was rude and dismissive but took my money. It happens. None of this is terrible. But our bill for two nights was about $500. I purchased the pet package which I assumed was just the pet fee. I am not sure that is true because I think it was more than the pet fee, but there was nothing extra included for the extra expense. I'm an old lady and maybe have some of this wrong. I have a lot of trouble navigating Green Bay. I think it would help if hotels with multiple exits post a sign as to which street they are exiting to and what direction is runs. Provide a decent city map too with directions to highlights from your hotel. GPS is not all that helpful when going through roundabout after roundabout and your passenger is disabled and not able to help much. My dumb phone refused to connect to Bluetooth and he had to try to read the directions. That did not work and we were lost trying to find places we wanted to visit and just wasted so much time. Not the hotel's fault. But overall the trip was not enjoyable. It's a great place if you are attending something at the convention center.  We thought this downtown location would be great for us, but I couldn't walk far with my back so it was not convenient for us.; ; ; ; ; ;The service was excellent, very friendly staff,  food was good, delivered promptly and although they forgot the salad dressing, that was remedied in minutes. We were too tired to go downstairs after a very long day and it was a very nice experience.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column239:
Soap spatters on mirrors and dried soap scum on bathroom counter. No extra roll of toilet paper in room. Two partial rolls were on the dispenser. 
Issues with the heat working BUT the maintenance man was fast in taking care of the issue and making sure our room was warmed up with a very nice portable heater.
The bed was not the most comfortable, my back is still out of commission and I am unable to do too much at this time. 
Bedding was thin, lack of blankets. 
Now, don't get me wrong, we really do like the hotel, but you did ask.

My name is Kolton, and I am the Assistant Front Office Manager for the Hyatt Regency Green Bay. 

Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback, and I sincerely apologize for the issues you experienced during your recent stay. We understand how disappointing it can be when a stay does not meet your expectations, especially when it’s a place you’ve enjoyed before. I’m truly sorry for the inconveniences you encountered.

Regarding the breakfast, I apologize for the misunderstanding. While we’ve made changes to our breakfast offerings for certain membership levels, we certainly understand how important this is for families. Your comments will help us ensure better communication about these changes moving forward. If you can forward where you saw that breakfast was included with your room, it would be greatly appreciated so we can get this updated to not cause further confusion. 

I’m also very sorry for the issues with the air conditioning and the toilet in your room. This is definitely not the standard we aim to provide. Our maintenance team will be investigating the room to ensure everything is in proper working order.

Your feedback is valuable to us, and I can assure you that we will be addressing these issues to improve the experience for future guests. If you’re open to it, we’d love to have the opportunity to make things right. Please feel free to reach out to me directly, and improve your stays in the future.

Sincerely,

2025-04-07 08:32:34] Email received from: "Olson, Lisa" <Lisa.Olson@SevitaHealth.com>: Hi Steven,
I appreciate you reaching out.  I do want to share that the quality of the food was not of concern.  It was presented well and tasted amazing.  I was a bit frustrated though that I waited for about 15 minutes for the yogurt to be refilled and actually had to tell the server it was out.  Once it came, I grabbed utensils and went to my seat, only to find that there wasn't a spoon in the rolled up utensils.  Upon returning to the buffet, I shared with a server that I needed a spoon, they handed me another rolled up utensil pack, but I told them there wasn't spoons in there.  They insisted there was and actually unrolled a set to prove it to me.  I think they felt a bit silly when they saw that indeed, there wasn't a spoon.  I was one of the last ones that went through the line, so I anticipate that others gave up and ate with a fork.  Two people said they would get me a spoon, but again - this took quite a while to retrieve.  Perhaps not a huge issue, but an area for improvement in the prep.
With you being in charge of food/beverages, I do want to share that my biggest concern was with the condition of the hotel room itself, items left behind by a previous guest that led me to have concerns, especially after seeing the amount of dust behind the side table when I dropped my cell phone in between the bed/side table.
I never complain or give negative feedback, but given other peers that also stayed had issues, I felt you would want the feedback.
Lisa

; ; ; ; ;My sister, my aunt, my two kids and myself have been coming and staying for the last 5 years a weekend to celebrate my kid's birthdays. So it is a tradition every year to stay at your fine establishment in Green Bay Wisconsin. We will be continuing this tradition for many years to come. 

Anastasia at the front desk is always a friendly face to see. She always has a smile on her face and she went above and beyond. I hope she will be there every time we come to stay in the future. Hope to see her next year. She is a rockstar.;You guys have the most comfortable beds. I absolutely love the pillows, sheets and comforters.  I would like to know what kind of pillows, sheets, and comforters you guys use so I can purchase some for at home.; ; ; ; ; ;The big soft pretzel so amazing. The only thing I did wish was that there was more salt but it still was absolutely amazing. The shrimp tacos were so delicious.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ;The thermostat in the room was not functioning. The fan was blowing all night at a temperature that was not comfortable, also making the environment very dry.; ; ;I wasn’t impressed from the moment I walked in. When I was trying to check in, there were two lines & two attendants. There was a sign marked world of Hyatt discoverist, explorist & globalist members, so that’s where I fell in line since I am a discoverist member. It should be noted that there was an attendant at the computer in front of the line that I was in. That attendant proceeded to move to another computer and started pulling other customers from the main line (not the line I was in for world of Hyatt members) & these were customers who had arrived after me. When one of the customers in the main line so kindly let me in front, I asked the attendant what even is the point of having a separate line for WOH members & she said there is only one line from which they operate from. Which is super silly because it was very clear that WOH discoverist & etc members were to fall in line there. But also both attendants knew I was present before the three people they checked in prior to me so It was not a good start to spend 20 min for the check-in process. 


The second thing I’d like to mention is the noise level at night time. On our first night, there was drag racing outside, which made it extremely difficult to put my young kids to sleep & settle in myself. I texted the front desk & they offered to switch rooms &/or bring up ear plugs. At that point, it was too late to switch rooms but it was very kind of the front desk. I was hoping they would call the non-emergent hotline for Green Bay PD to shut down the drag races outside. When I brought up the issue to the front desk in the morning, the attendant informed me that it is a normal occurrence, and that if it happens tonight that I, the customer, should be the one to call Green Bay Police Department, which seems very silly to put that responsibility on me.; ;Green Bay Regency does not honor the dedicated check-in area for discoverist & above members. Why even have the separated lines if you’re going to ignore my presence completely? And then act as if there is no process to expedite members’ check-in. I was looking forward to reaping that reward as I had two young children, which can be very stressful in traveling.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column76: Wouldn’t recommend (especially if you’re a WOH globalist or above member)
column77:
Our stay was extremely subpar. The only pro to our stay was the indoor pool area. 

Here were the cons: 
I spent 20 min for th check-in process. They did not honor the expedited check-in line for WOH Discoverist, Explorist & Globalist members. When I finally was helped, they acted like they didn’t have two separate line sections & that it was my fault for not falling into the main line. 

Elevators are extremely slow. The only reason we didn’t take the stairs because it was so far from the elevator area & we stayed on the 8th floor. You may think it’s a silly thing to write about but if you stay there, you’ll see it truly is a nuisance.

The thermostat does not allow for any personalization. The fan blew all night, making it such a dry environment. My children & I left with sniffles because of it. It seems as if the facility is pretty outdated. Carpets were in poor condition. Popcorn ceiling in full effect —how is that still a thing in the luxury hotels? 

The worst thing is that the noise level at night is extremely disruptive. Close to 11 PM, there were drag races occurring outside. It made it difficult to put my young kids down, let alone settle in myself. When I contacted the front desk that evening, they offered to switch our room &/or send up ear plugs (which was super accommodating, I will acknowledge). In the morning, when I went to get my two free water bottles of the day, the attendant asked how my night went. I mentioned the noise level, & she said that it is a regular occurrence, and that I should call the non-emergent Green Bay Police department, if it were to happen that following evening. It seems silly to put that responsibility on the customer. The front desk should call Green Bay PD themselves.

We stayed at this Hyatt as a stay-cation but don’t think we will return. For close to 20k points redemption, it was not worth it. I had high hopes for this Hyatt Regency but you’re better off using points for other Hyatts.

column64: ; ; ;The room was far too hot. We turned down the thermostat but after 7 hours the room did not cool down at all. We complained at the front desk at 1130pm because we couldn't sleep from the heat. An hour later there still was no relief from the heat and no service person had been in contact to give an update. We called down to the front desk and they said the guy must've been having problems with his walkie and they would call his cell. At this point it was 1230am and we needed to get to sleep so we asked for a fan to be brought up. The guy who delivered the fan said we could open the sliding door (which had no screen) to help cool down the room. The heating issue was never fixed nor did it seem like they were even working on fixing it at all the whole weekend we were there. We mentioned the heating issue again at check out and the front desk person just ignored it and continued with the check out process without even acknowledging the issue. Also, the toilets cannot possibly be ADA compliant. They were far too low in the rooms. The seats only came about half way up my calf. Overall, I would not stay at that location again unless that was literally the only option in all of Green Bay. The food in the restaurant was far too expensive. $17 for eggs and bacon is excessive.;Any action to fix the heating issue would have been better than the lack of action that was present during our stay.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

This was a huge disappointment and made sleeping just about impossible without ear plugs.; ; ; ; ; ;I got a to go order so I did not experience the in restaurant experience. column239:
The room was cold when I checked into it. Hotel staff fixed this by offering a space heater which seemed odd. They assisted further by stopping the flow of air which ultimately worked to warm the room. The number of space heaters used in this hotel is ridiculous. There was a large, wide dirty streak on the ceiling from the continuous air flow into the room. I cannot imagine the last time you cleaned the ducting system. 

The sheets and towels were clean as wet other touch surfaces however room corners were dirty. The hallways were seldom vacuumed outside of the actual room doorway and the elevators contained the same surface dropped materials during my six night stay. 

Staff were great but the deeper cleaning which is common in hotels just didn’t occur at this Hyatt.

Sometimes things are forgotten to be grabbed on the way and you don't notice right away. Even with 24/7 access to such items in the lobby, going down 8 floors when you want a late snack is not always.; ;There don't seem to be any "real" perks -- and they may be there -- it may be beneficial to have staff identify them.; ; ; ;I went down to have a drink or two at the bar, and while it was 10pm, there were clearly a group of people who had previously worked as bartenders complaining about the number and amount of tips they receive from some people at the bars they work at. While it is not related to the bar itself, and the bartender did not engage them, the nature of the conversation visibly made even the bartender feel uncomfortable. I ended up taking two cans of High Noon to my room to avoid pronounced their chatter. It's something as a patron that you just don't want to think about at a bar -- the other side of the bar and the tips they receive at a different bar. Anyone in a professional business capacity, or their clients, would have been uncomfortable.;Even with room service, and a full bar, creating a concept that places such items in a room is nothing new, but there has to be a way to make it convenient and beneficial for everyone. As stated previously, there is nothing worse than wanting a late-night snack, drink of juice, soda, water, and having zero desire to travel down 8 floors to obtain it.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

; ; ; ; ; ;Unfortunately, the rooms are due for a much needed update. I had just come from the Hyatt Regency in Jacksonville where the rooms were much nicer and the staff was phenomenal, so the comparison was noticeable. The food at Pub33 was not good at all. I understand the need to have a limited menu when having so many people present for a large event, but the food and service was significantly lacking. I hate to provide such honest feedback that isn’t positive… 

On the plus side, the front desk was very responsive when resolving an issue with the bill.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ;Refrigerator stopped working toward end of our stay.; ; ;I made a reservation in June not knowing if I would need 2 or 3 nights for my February stay.  Found out 2 weeks prior, I only need 2 so tried to cancel one night on Thursday and was told I would need to pay 40 more overall to cancel one night and when I said I could see charging me the same total for the 2 nights as 3 (in essence I pay the same whether I stay the 3 nights on my reservation or 2) but not more as I had a reservation for 3 nights and if I showed up Thursday it would be the quoted rate but because I can't check in until Friday I suddenly have to pay what I was paying for 3 nights(even though I'm now staying 2) plus 40 more when you can resell the Thursday night room besides.  The staff was rude, said rates were only going to ho up more and refused my request to speak with a manager to get clarification so I booked elsewhere.  Around 3 days later your rates went to 50 less per night than what my original reservation was for so I switched back only because my event was at your location but if the staff had been kind and honored my rate I would have paid you 50 more a night because I would have no reason to shop around an i would be happy.  I now feel like I was being scammed.
On a side note, the housekeepers were very friendly which is not something you see in many hotels.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

When checking into Hyatt Regency Green Bay, we place a temporary authorization of $50 per night on your credit or debit card. This hold covers any incidental charges you may incur during your stay, such as dining, parking or the event damages are found to the room. This is not an actual charge-- any unused portion of the authorization is released after checkout. However, the timing of the release depends on your bank's processing time, which may take a few business days.  The total amount charged for your stay was $197.51 and should balance out within a few days. You can reach out to your banking institution for a better understanding of a timeline. column64: ; ; ;Facility is showing it's age.  Screwed in panels in ceiling of shower,  shampoo / soap not filled, bubbles in carpeting, water so hard it does not foam, tvs / remotes only sort of work, no provided wifi information, fitness center equipment outdated (32pin ipod connectors), etc.  overall the appearance is like lipstick on a pig - looks pretty but underneath it's shabby and old;Stay out of my room.  When i put up a do not disturb, i expect no room service, not a note that says they come in every 24 hours no matter what. I was there 5 nights. I prefer privacy and want to keep my room private for the entirety of my stay, unless there is an actual emergency that requires room service.; ;The entire facility is super outdated.  Everything shows it age. Also, very poor overall planning. There is a mirror in the bedroom, but no nearby plug.  the only plug at that counter has no mirror. the bathroom has no exhaust fan. The rooms are very drafty and cold, even with the heat cranked. I had to use both comforters and my own personal blankets just to stay warm at night. No extra bedding provided for the sleeper sofa, or I would have used that blanket too.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Our room was not up to the standard of a Hyatt hotel. The room itself was a corner room and was not like the other rooms in the Hyatt of Green Bay. ( 2 room set up). It was one big room with one couch, one desk chair, very little lighting, and the few pieces of furniture were worn, chipped, and mismatching.  We had difficulty getting on and off the toilet as it was so low. On the bright side, the beds were very comfortable,and the shower and towels were nice.  It was almost like the room we were in was an afterthought filled with mismatched furniture and odds and ends.  We will have a difficult time staying here again.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Occasionally, our blankets may show rust stains from being used on the sofa beds/getting caught in the metal pieces, but this is not typical, and we are actively working to address it. Regardless, we will certainly follow up with our housekeeping and laundry teams to ensure more care and attention detail is present when preparing linens for our rooms.

column64: ; ; ; ;this is the second wedding that i have attended at the Hyatt in Green Bay. both had open bars. the house brand of vodka and whiskey were so putrid at both events there was not enough mix in the building to make them palatable to drink. The food at the reception was cold and the soup and salad on one side of the room and the main course on the opposite side was not communicated to guests. The only reason we discovered it was that the line was so long we went to the other side. The food was tough and cold. I’ve had better food and drink at dive bars in Wisconsin at a fraction of the cost. Would never recommend you establishment for any event; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

2025-01-02 20:12:17] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Julie Peick,

My name is Breton Spiller, and I am the Guest Experience Specialist here at Hyatt Regency Green Bay. Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. Your comments are incredibly valuable as they help us continually improve and ensure a better experience for all of our guests.

I’m truly sorry to hear about the temperature issue in your room. Unfortunately, our HVAC system operates on a centralized system, which can sometimes make it difficult to control individual room temperatures. I can imagine how uncomfortable this must have been. If you had reached out to our team about this, I do apologize if they did not offer a fan during your stay, as we always have them available for guests to ensure they are as comfortable as can be. 

I also understand your frustration with the parking fee. While the $10 parking charge is intended to cover the convenience and security of our on-site parking, I recognize it was an unexpected cost in light of the other issues you experienced. As a gesture of goodwill, I am happy to refund this charge as a one-time courtesy. Please allow up to two business days for the refund to be reflected on your account.

Regarding the domestic incident you mentioned, I deeply regret any concern or discomfort it caused. Your safety and well-being are our top priority, and I can assure you that our security team, in collaboration with local authorities, was able to de-escalate the situation. We have taken note of the individuals involved and will take appropriate action to prevent any future disturbances.

Lastly, I’m sorry to hear about your experience with the hot tub and sauna. This is certainly not the standard we strive to maintain, and I have shared your feedback with our maintenance team so they can investigate and resolve the issue as quickly as possible.

Thank you once again for your valuable feedback. We truly hope to have the opportunity to welcome you back and provide a more seamless experience. If you have any additional concerns or need further assistance, please don’t hesitate to reach out to me directly.

Sincerely,

Breton Spiller
